HPLC assay was used to confirm the accuracy of electrochemical method, which was a common and predominant analytical method for the quantification of nucleobases and their analogs [41,42]. HPLC method was employed to determine the mixture of UA, G, X, A and HX with retention times of 8.74, 13.79, 15.26, 28.03 and 12.28 min, respectively (
                        Fig. S4
                        ), and the calibration parameters of the five substances were listed in Table S2.
